{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"35a515f3-ecb7-4a1f-baa0-7a3129d75528","content":"The template is **not quite ready** for NuGet publishing. Here are the issues:\n\n**Missing required field:**\n- `$schema` — recommended for validation/tooling support\n- `\"preferNameDirectory\": true` — recommended for `dotnet new`\n\n**Critical missing field:**\n- **`groupIdentity`** — needed if you plan multiple language/framework variants\n\n**Should fix before publishing:**\n1. **No `description`** — NuGet and `dotnet new` search rely on this for discoverability.\n2. **No `defaultName`** — controls the default project name when none is specified.\n3. **`sourceName` doesn't match identity convention** — minor, but worth verifying it matches your template source folder.\n\n**Looks good:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `classifications`, `tags`, and `symbols` are all well-formed.\n\n**Minimum fix** — add a `description` and the `$schema` reference:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\",\n  \"description\": \"A template for creating a Web API project.\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nOnce you add `description` (and ideally `defaultName` and `preferNameDirectory`), it's publishable.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1870bd33-cd6f-4f2e-9ea8-3a6916a35f1c","outputTokens":295,"requestId":"740C:2131E5:1C25C31:1F2EAFB:69FA90E5"},"id":"73315248-789c-44a8-8e5d-547b3a8888f2","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:53:01.779Z","parentId":"55a5b51c-892d-4312-bd3a-c1650b845cf2"}
